The National Lotteries Commission office in Pretoria is being raided by the Special Investigating Unit and the Hawks. eNCA's Barry Bateman is there. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The National Lotteries Commission offices in Pretoria is being raided. The raid is a joint operation between the Special Investigating Unit and the Hawks. President Cyril Ramaphosa issued the gazette for the investigation in October to look into allegations of corruption, fraud, and tender irregularities dating back to 2014. For more details on the story, watch the video above. 